# Show preview of changes BEFORE asking for confirmation

## Context

Interactive prompts that ask yes/no should show what will happen first

## Pattern

When asking user to confirm a destructive action, first show the list of affected items (files to delete, hooks to remove, etc.), then ask for confirmation.

## Example

```typescript
console.log('Files that will be removed:');
for (const f of filesToDelete) {
  console.log(`  - ${f.path}`);
}
console.log('(These are safe to remove)');
const confirmed = await askQuestion('Proceed? [y/N] ');
```

## Why

Asking 'Clean up duplicates? [y/N]' without showing WHICH duplicates forces user to guess or abort. Preview builds confidence in the decision.
